article.description: Allie LeClaire scored 16 points, Jessica Lindstrom added 13 and No. 20 Green Bay beat Milwaukee 65-36 on Saturday for its 11th straight win.
article.headline: No. 20 Green Bay women have no trouble with Milwaukee 65-36
article.linkText: No. 20 Green Bay women have no trouble with Milwaukee 65-36
article.story:
MILWAUKEE --  Allie LeClaire scored 16 points, Jessica Lindstrom added 13 and No. 20 Green Bay beat Milwaukee 65-36 on Saturday for its 11th straight win.

LeClaire was 6 of 9 from the field with two 3-pointers and had five assists and three rebounds. Lindstrom was 5 of 8 from 3, with five rebounds and four assists.

The Phoenix (22-2, 12-1 Horizon League) closed the first quarter with a 10-0 run to lead 18-8 and had a 14-2 run, including the last seven points of the second quarter, to lead 34-17 at the break. With the first 13 points of the third, Green Bay had a 20-0 run to make it 47-17.

The Panthers went from the 7:14 mark of the second quarter to 2:01 of the third between field goals, missing 15 straight shots.

No player had more than seven points for the Panthers (17-8, 8-5), who shot 11 of 40.
